JOHANNESBURG (miningweekly.com) &ndash; Platinum group metals miner Eurasia has lodged a discovery certificate with the Russian State Agency for Subsoil use (Rosendra) for its Monchetundra palladium and platinum project. This certificate assigns mining rights for the associated reserves to the holder and covers all reserves and resources approved by Rosendra. The mine holds 1.9-million ounces in palladium equivalent, with major additional gold and base metal credits, at two openpittable locations.